    Introduction

    We apply the package ensBagg to a data set The Bone Marrow Transplant Data (bmt) which is in the package timereg . Bone marrow transplants are a standard treatment for acute leukemia. In the recovery process patients can suffer from Infections, toxicity, and (after allogeneic HSCT only), graft-vs.-host disease (GVHD) being the main causes of death. We are interested in predicting the time to death related to treatment where the risk of relapse is a competing risk.

    Setup

    We load the package ensBagg and timereg and we load the data set bmt

    library(ensBagg)
library(timereg)
#> Loading required package: survival
bmt.data <- data(bmt)

tao=7
